text:
I’ve been noticing that I tend to spend a disproportionate amount of time in my personal projects trying to figure out the UX look and feel.

I have very little difficulty translating well made designs into whatever framework I’m working in, but struggle with creating those designs, especially when starting from scratch.

Are there any resources, advice, or mindsets you can give/recommend to help me improve this part of the process?

You can't recover your Google account if you lose your 2FA device
text:
I have a Google account which used a phone number I no longer have for 2FA. I have the correct password to it, but can't login to it without 2FA. Google sends me to an account recovery sequence when I try to regain control over the account, but there's actually no way to complete this either without the phone. Of course there's no human support available. The only "suggestion" they provide is to create a new Google account, which certainly isn't helpful...

Screenshot attached. (Email address in that screenshot has been blanked out). https://imgur.com/a/OT1pqy9

To be clear, I still have access to the email address in question and could certainly retrieve any recovery code they send there. They don't offer that option though. Phone or nothing.

How can we make dark mode work well with multiple windows?
text:
I'm a dark mode fan. It's easier on the eyes. But one thing that dark mode doesn't excel at is easily showing the difference between multiple windows. With light mode, this can be done with shadows behind the stacked windows. Gives them depth and helps you see where one window ends and another begins. But with dark mode I find that this distinction is very difficult to show or see.

Any ideas for making multiple stacked windows, all with dark mode on, more distinct from one another?
